pc. The observed bursts characteristics and source accretion\nrate suggest pure helium explosions igniting at column depths y_{ign} ~ 0.8-4.8\n10^8 g cm^-1, for typical energy releases of ~1.2-7.4 10^39 erg.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 19 Jun 2009 10:29:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-13"}
